<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1874,2027]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This group could be charactirised in the combination of the following characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Grootaert" box="[1137,1386,1874,1900]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Grootaert" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="55 - 61" refId="ref69044" refString="Grootaert P., Cumming J. &amp; Shamshev I. 2007. Non-marine Chersodromia Walker from Southeast Asia and Papua New Guinea (Diptera, Empidoidea, Hybotidae). Zootaxa 1661: 55 - 61." type="journal article" year="2007">
Grootaert 
<emphasis box="[1258,1316,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
): body very pale, almost white; eyes touching on the face, wing with vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1067,1076,1934,1948]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">1</subScript>
very short and ending well before middle of wing, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[485,511,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">2+3</subScript>
meeting costa before or near middle of wing, consequently, Rs shorter than in other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker, 1849:" authorityYear="1157" box="[287,453,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chersodromia</taxonomicName>
